<h4>At the end of one of the services during the April 2010 annual  convention of Helping Inspire Ministries (H.I.M.), Rev. Elizabeth  Pruitt-Sloan gives the following message in tongues, while pausing to  give the audience instructions, then Brother Mel interprets the message  in tongues.  This is an example of a situation in which a message could  be communicated in &#8220;another tongue,&#8221; but which takes considerably more  words in the English language to communicate that same message:</h4>
