			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" title="Jesus--sand.jpg" src="http://brothermel.podbean.com/mf/web/33uz36/Jesus--sand.jpg" border="0" alt="Jesus--sand.jpg" width="266" height="242" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
</p><p style="text-align: center;">
</p><p style="text-align: left;">Brother Mel  preached the this message at the opening service of the H.I.M. Annual  Ministers Convention.  He began by describing to the assembled  ministers aspects of the current Great Awakening that is in the earth,  and comparing it with previous moves of God.  He told about two of the  three recent angelic visitations he had experienced, and what he  believed they meant.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Then he  launched into a message in which he confronted, and comforted, the  listeners by warning and exhorting them to learn from the moves of the  past, and the mistakes thereof, so that they do not sit out the current  move.  He spoke about two of the three biblical truths that had been  emphasized to him by the Lord since the angelic visitations.</p>
<p>Brother Mel concluded by describing a vision the Lord gave him years  ago of a powerful evil spirit that works against Christians, hindering  them from receiving from God.  He concluded by sharing a testimony of  personal revival and breakthrough, and invited ministers to come forward  to seek the Lord, and to be prayed for to receive newness in God.  Many  ministers came forward, and the recording includes the time of personal  ministry, prayer, and the operation of spiritual gifts.</p>
<p>Mel reports that the Lord ministered deeply to fellow  ministers, saying that as he preached, &#8220;I could see psychological,  mental, and spiritual loads visibly lift off of various ministers, and  their countenances brightened like the difference between night and  day.&#8221;</p>
<p>For more materials by Brother Mel, please visit <a href="http://www.brothermel.com">www.brothermel.com</a> or the &#8220;Voices of the Faith Giants Podcast&#8221; at <a href="http://brothermel.podbean.com">http://brothermel.podbean.com</a>.
</p>
